, often his stores are the most fashionable places to shop and his residential designs are artfully placed within their settings. This publication is of special interest not only for the practising architect or historian but, with its strong visuals and informal style, accessible and entertaining for anyone eager to celebrate our architectural heritage.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aArchitectszCanadavBiography. 0aArchitectszEnglandvBiography. 0aArchitecture, Moderny19th century. 7aARCHITECTURE / Individual Architects & Firms / Monographs.2bisacsh1 aSzamosi, Annie, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077359607840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773596078423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773596078/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles